7. I changed the setting.json, not work.
8. Update line 9 to "python", debugger will work.

in the extension [markdown](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/master/extensions/markdown/src/extension.ts) ,

```
let d3 = vscode.commands.registerCommand('markdown.showSource', showSource);
```

no parameter was passed to the showSource , 

``` ts
function showSource(mdUri: Uri) {
    if (!mdUri) {
        return vscode.commands.executeCommand('workbench.action.navigateBack');
    }

    const docUri = Uri.parse(mdUri.query);

    for (let editor of vscode.window.visibleTextEditors) {
        if (editor.document.uri.toString() === docUri.toString()) {
            return vscode.window.showTextDocument(editor.document, editor.viewColumn);
        }
    }

    return vscode.workspace.openTextDocument(docUri).then(doc => {
        return vscode.window.showTextDocument(doc);
    });
}
```

is it possible to execute the code after if{....}.
Any help will be appreciated!

- VSCode Version: 1.4.0
- OS Version: OS X 10.11.6

Steps to Reproduce:
- Create an extension with the following code

``` javascript
  let vscode = require('vscode');
  let window = vscode.window;

  let decorationTypeOne = window.createTextEditorDecorationType({
    isWholeLine: true, // not relevant, but present in the real-world scenario
  });
  let decorationTypeTwo = window.createTextEditorDecorationType({
    color: 'green'
  });

  let decorationWithContent = {
    range: new vscode.Range(0, 0, 0, 3),
    renderOptions: {after: {contentText: '+test'}}
  };

  let decorationWithColor = {range: new vscode.Range(0, 1, 0, 2)};

  window.activeTextEditor.setDecorations(decorationTypeOne, [decorationWithContent]);
  window.activeTextEditor.setDecorations(decorationTypeTwo, [decorationWithColor]);
```
- Open a text file with a single line `abc` in it.
- The result is a duplicated `contentText` inserted in a middle of the text.

<img width="188" alt="screen shot 2016-08-22 at 2 16 59 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/979966/17843609/53ec5f38-6873-11e6-9433-cc2973558904.png">

Note if you remove `color: 'green'` from the second decoration type, then it works as expected:

<img width="122" alt="screen shot 2016-08-22 at 2 25 16 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/979966/17843692/4ed1046c-6874-11e6-9db7-2dde0d57fe47.png">

Real-world scenario was reported [in wallaby.js repo](https://github.com/wallabyjs/public/issues/751#issuecomment-241301408) where decorations inserted by wallaby are broken when [Rainbow Brackets](https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=2gua.rainbow-brackets) extension is also used, which simply adds colours to certain ranges.
